Roatus <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uroatusbh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoatusBH</A> at: 6/15/01 2:35:18 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uselilya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>selilya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FFFF66>Board Moderator<br><font color=#A0B0E0>&lt;Violent Harvest&gt;  </font></span><br>  Posts: 596<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/15/01 2:41:44 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/selilya/sel_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Need some advice for plane reservation /sigh</span><hr size=1> Goodness...there are too many threads on this issue.  I've posted this suggestion on the other threads too.<br>
<br>
I have a solution that's simple. <br>
<br>
Block off two consective weekday nights once a month and block off two consecutive weekend nights once a month, solely for NON-US majority guilds. The guilds would compete for the spots (or hopefully work things out with each other). This does several things. Most patches will be on weekdays, I believe. This give them a shot there. Also, weekends tend to give a guild a bit more flexibility with their players.<br>
<br>
Now, many folks have whined about not getting shots in the planes. I beg to differ. I think every Fear or Hate raid I hear about has 5 to 45 percent no-shows. These people have no room to complain, if they were offered a valid slot, and did not attend. Most don't even bother to inform the raid leader. I'm keeping a list of those who don't show and fail to tell me ahead of time. They won't be invited back any time soon.<br>
<br>
I think this is a workable compromise that insures everyone gets some access to planar experience.<br>
<br>
So...how about NON-US getting the 1st Fri/Sat of each month and the 3rd Tue/Wed of each month? That's not a lot to ask. <br>
<br>
Some of us are trying to find a way to accomodate just about everyone.  Maybe it's a naive idea, but maybe it can work if folks calm down and think about it for a bit.  It'd be nice to be able to just go have some fun.<br>
<br>
<br>
